-- Khazanah, Actis to Invest 8.4 Billion Rupees in IDFC, Economic Times Says
-- Abhishek Shanker
-- 2010-07-08T01:51:48Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-08/khazanah-actis-to-invest-8-4-billion-rupees-in-idfc-economic-times-says.html

          
          
             Infrastructure Development Finance 
Company Ltd. will sell convertible securities to Khazanah 
Nasional Bhd. and Actis LLP at 176 rupees a share to raise 8.4 
billion rupees, the Economic Times reported citing Vikram 
Limaye, executive director at Infrastructure Development.  
